                  "alignItems": "center",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "gx47a",
                      "fill": "$foreground-tertiary",
                      "content": "March 15, 2026",
                      "fontFamily": "Geist Mono",
                      "fontSize": 13,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "ellipse",
                      "id": "8olNG",
                      "fill": "$foreground-tertiary",
                      "width": 3,
                      "height": 3
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "HY2SM",
                      "fill": "$foreground-tertiary",
                      "content": "5 min read",
                      "fontFamily": "Geist Mono",
                      "fontSize": 13,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "1Kk3d",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Building Scalable Systems with Clean Architecture",
                  "lineHeight": 1.2,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 36,
                  "fontWeight": "800",
                  "letterSpacing": -1
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "gtnmy",
                  "fill": "$foreground-secondary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "An exploration of how clean architecture principles help build maintainable, testable software systems that stand the test of time.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.7,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 17,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "id": "5zb8T",
                  "fill": "$border-subtle",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "height": 1
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "4t1Yq",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Software architecture is the foundation upon which all code is built. Without a clear architectural vision, projects inevitably devolve into tangled dependency graphs that resist change and breed bugs. Clean Architecture offers a disciplined approach to organizing code that keeps business logic at the center while pushing infrastructure concerns to the edges.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "hKZCX",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The Dependency Rule",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "R2N22",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "The fundamental rule is simple: source code dependencies must point inward. Nothing in an inner circle can know anything about something in an outer circle. Your business rules don't know about the database, the UI, or any external framework.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "zLwxE",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Practical Implementation in .NET",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "AdDZX",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "In a .NET solution, this manifests as separate projects: Domain, Application, Infrastructure, and API. MediatR serves as the messaging backbone, routing commands and queries to their handlers without tight coupling.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "nweUx",
                  "name": "lgDCode",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "$surface-elevated",
                  "cornerRadius": 8,
                  "stroke": {
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "$border-subtle"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "padding": 20,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "i8zIW",
                      "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "public class CreatePostHandler\n    : IRequestHandler<CreatePost, PostDto>\n{\n    private readonly IBlogDbContext _context;\n\n    public async Task<PostDto> Handle(\n        CreatePost request,\n        CancellationToken ct)\n    {\n        var post = new Post(request.Title);\n        _context.Posts.Add(post);\n        await _context.SaveChangesAsync(ct);\n        return post.ToDto();\n    }\n}",
                      "lineHeight": 1.6,
                      "fontFamily": "Geist Mono",
                      "fontSize": 13,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "R1uZX",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Conclusion",
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 24,
                  "fontWeight": "700",
                  "letterSpacing": -0.5
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "gyZQ8",
                  "fill": "$foreground-primary",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Clean Architecture isn't a silver bullet, but it's one of the most effective tools for building systems that survive contact with changing requirements. Start with the dependency rule, build outward, and let your domain drive the design.",
                  "lineHeight": 1.8,
                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                  "fontSize": 16,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "id": "lvNtn",
                  "fill": "$border-subtle",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "height": 1
                },
